<div class="dablink">This article is about the World War II nuclear project.  For other uses of the name "The Manhattan Project", see <a href="/wiki/Manhattan_Project_(disambiguation)" title="Manhattan Project (disambiguation)">Manhattan Project (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<table class="infobox vcard" style="width: 315px; border-spacing: 2px; text-align: left; font-size: 90%;">
<tr>
<th class="fn org" colspan="2" style="background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;">Manhattan Engineer District (MED)</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align: center; font-size: 90%; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa; line-height: 1.5em;"><a href="/wiki/File:Trinity_shot_color.jpg" class="image" title="Trinity shot color.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Trinity_shot_color.jpg/200px-Trinity_shot_color.jpg" width="200" height="250" border="0" /></a><br />
The <strong class="selflink">Manhattan Project</strong> created the first <a href="/wiki/Nuclear_bomb" title="Nuclear bomb" class="mw-redirect">nuclear bombs</a>, and the first human-engineered <a href="/wiki/Trinity_(nuclear_test)" title="Trinity (nuclear test)">nuclear detonation</a>.</td>
</tr>
